            <div id="why-call-tracking" class="mt-8">
              <h2 class="font-heading font-semibold text-2xl mb-4">Why Call Tracking Matters for HVAC Companies</h2>
              <p class="text-sm text-foreground/80 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                The average HVAC company spends $2,000–$8,000/month on marketing across Google Ads, Local Service Ads, SEO, and referral programs. Without call tracking, you have no way to know which channel generated each phone call. You are essentially flying blind.
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-foreground/80 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                Call tracking assigns unique phone numbers to each marketing source. When a homeowner calls, you instantly know whether they found you through a Google Ad, an organic search result, your LSA listing, or a yard sign. This data lets you double down on what works and cut what does not.
              </p>
              <div class="bg-muted/50 border border-border rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
                <h4 class="data-label text-foreground mb-2">Real-World Example</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-foreground/70">
                  A 6-tech HVAC company in Dallas discovered through CallRail that 40% of their Google Ads budget was going to a campaign that generated zero booked jobs. They reallocated that $1,200/month to their top-performing campaign and increased booked calls by 25% without spending more.
                </p>
              </div>
